Filter Pods by Node  
kubectl get pods -A -o wide | grep ip-10-0-1-25

Delete a node
cordon → stop new traffic
drain  → move running apps
delete → shutdown server

Step 1 — Cordon Node
kubectl cordon <node-name>
Step 2 — Drain Node
kubectl drain <node-name> --ignore-daemonsets --delete-local-data

kubectl scale --replicas=6 deployment demo-nginx
kubectl delete pod demo-nginx-686d55c7f-bkdgp
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods
